SIMPLE: charivari
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Charivari
<hw>Cha*ri`va*ri"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<def>A mock serenade of discordant noises, made with kettles, tin horns,
etc., designed to annoy and insult; -- called also
<altname>shivaree</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> shivaree, charivari, callithump,
callathump.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ It was at first performed before the house of any person
of advanced age who married a second time.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chark</ent>⟦br⟧
